# Code Standards

## Organization
- Extract reusable logic into `util` or `helper` files when it could be used in multiple places
- Avoid duplicating helper functions across files

## Style
- Be concise — avoid verbose or redundant code
- Optimize for performance
- Use explicit TypeScript types when appropriate (avoid excessive `any` usage)

## Communication
- Ask clarifying questions if requirements or implementation approach is unclear
